Male.
Pygophore slightly constricted dorsolaterally around bases of dorsolateral lobes (
Fig. 30G–I
). Ventral rim with median broadly bilobed process (
Fig. 30G
). Anterior flange of dorsolateral lobe poorly developed as small rounded carina (
Fig. 30I
); posterior lobes absent; posteroventral lobes acute, rounded, directed laterally (
Fig. 30G–I
). Medial penile plates little more than 2X longer than broad; basal half or medial area carinate; distal portion slightly swollen with small medial carina (
Fig. 33C
).

Female.
Laterotergites of eighth segment with small pair of lobes. Posterior margin of gonocoxa of eighth segment extremely sinuate. Gonocoxa of ninth segment narrow; posterior margin distinctly emarginate. Laterotergites of ninth segment elongate, triangular apically (
Fig. 36C
). Secondary thickening of vagina intima short, 1.5–2X longer than broad, broadly bilobed distally, pore to ductus recepticali opening between lobes (
Fig. 35A
).
